raw_data.title: Program Manager
raw_data.description: Responsible for the performance of programs, projects, or subsystems of major programs or projects. Directs all phases of programs/projects from inception through completion. Coordinates the preparation of project plans, milestones, and operating budgets. Acts as primary customer contact for program activities, leading program review sessions with customer to discuss cost, schedule, and technical performance. Establishes design concepts, criteria, and engineering efforts for product research, development, integration, and test. Establishes milestones and monitors adherence to master plans and schedules. Identifies program problems and obtains solutions. Directs the work of technical, manufacturing, and administrative employees assigned to the program/project.

raw_data.title: Mechanical Engineer
raw_data.description: Independently designs and develops plans, processes, procedures and tools to operate systems/hardware.  Required to provide direction to less experienced engineers or lead projects.  Responsibilities include:  Independently applies creativity and engineering judgment in anticipating and solving unprecedented engineering problems, determining program objectives and requirements, organizing programs and projects, and developing standards and guides for diverse engineering activities.

raw_data.title: Electrical Engineer
raw_data.description: :  Supports production in designing, fabricating, inspecting, testing, and troubleshooting electrical items used on and or to maintain the Aerospace Life Support Systems.  Responsibilities include creativity and engineering judgment in anticipating and solving unprecedented engineering problems, determining program objectives and requirements, scheduling assigned work, organizing programs and projects, and developing standards and guides for diverse engineering activities.  This job requires knowledge of electrical components and fabrication techniques unique to spaceflight.

raw_data.title: Test Engineer
raw_data.description: Independently designs and develops plans, processes, procedures and tools to operate systems/hardware.  Provides direction in the test room to ensure safety of operations and personnel involved.  Responsibilities include planning testing of high altitude pressure suit garments, helmets and associate hardware, coordinating schedules of necessary personnel, training for unique testing not performed elsewhere, qualification testing of pressure garments and components, test equipment monitoring, and maintaining records.

raw_data.title: Pattern Designer
raw_data.description: The Pattern Designer is responsible for creating and designing patterns for aerospace crew protective equipment.  Assists senior designer(s) and engineer(s) with the original creation and development of safety and protective clothing. Creates, develops and prints design concepts utilizing Gerber CAD software.  Applies experience and data to the unique design of life saving garments.  Examines prototypes on and off models in a test room environment, and then modifies designs to achieve desired effects.  Assists production to ensure all details are addressed.  Assists in the creation of drawing and other controlled documentation.

raw_data.title: Technical Writer
raw_data.description: Collects and organizes information required for preparation of technical publications.  Provides out line of contents of technical publications, prepares written text, coordinates layout and organization of documents, obtains and interprets necessary data, drawings, and specifications through research and liaison with technical staff.

raw_data.title: Chemical Engineer
raw_data.description: Conducts laboratory tests and assists other chem lab technicians.  Analyze solids, liquids and gases for research and development.  Chemical Engineer will also provide assistance on chemical experimentation using techniques, such as physical and chemical separation, microscopy, spectroscopy and chromatography. Other responsibilities include result documentation.

raw_data.title: Quality Control
raw_data.description: Maintaining the quality and reliability of all company products, including life support equipment.  Quality control is also responsible for understanding detailed inspection drawings and unique testing of products at various stages in the production process not typically performed in any other industry.  Oversees all testing associated with the qualification of high altitude and space flight hardware.  Must train for an extended period of time before functions can be fulfilled independently.

raw_data.title: Model Maker
raw_data.description: Sets up and operates machines, such as lathes, drill presses, or band saws, to fabricate prototypes or models. Also determines fixtures, machines, tooling, and sequence of operations to fabricate parts, dies, and tooling, according to drawings and sketches.  Drills, countersinks, and reams holes in parts and assemblies for bolts, screw, and other fasteners, using power tools.  Responsible for fabrication of plastic and metal parts inspects.  Model maker is also responsible for verification of conformance to specifications, using precision measuring instruments or circuit tester.

raw_data.title: Laboratory Technician
raw_data.description: Responsible for analyzing technical issues and problems.  Technician is responsible for following and developing working procedures for unique aerospace life support equipment.  Employee will assist in production of chemicals needed for life support equipment manufacturing including, but not limited to mixing chemical solutions, molding elastomers, and creating prototype solutions and parts.  Technician will also maintain a safe and sterile laboratory environment.  Other responsibilities include documentation of test results.

raw_data.title: Assembly & Test Technician
raw_data.description: Responsible for analyzing technical issues and problems.  Technician is also responsible for reading prints and engineering documents as well as following and developing working procedures.  Employee will assist in production of life support equipment to specifications and have knowledge of flow meter and pressure gauge.  Technician will be directly involved with all productions of molded pieces, bladders, and other suit components.  Other responsibilities include:  following blueprints or assembly specifications and fabricate portions of a certain product.

raw_data.title: Electronic Sealer
raw_data.description: Performs tasking based on work orders and is under the direction of a technical team member with responsibility of designing and manufacturing aerospace life support equipment.  Sealer will work as a member of a technical team or separately under direct supervision.  Requires ability to read and interpret diagrams and detailed written instructions.  Must train and demonstrate operation of sealing machines with the necessary precision.

raw_data.title: Machinist
raw_data.description: Performs tasking based on work orders and is under the direction of a technical team member.  Machinist will work as a member of a technical team or separately under direct supervision.  Other responsibilities include:  examining blueprints and looking for inaccuracies, create new parts for various models and machines, and maintain compliance with all facility/local/state/federal safety standards.  Performs the less complex machining operations, including working with computerized equipment and plays a more significant role in the design of prototype instruments.3

raw_data.title: Cutter
raw_data.description: Performs tasking based on work orders and is under the direction of a technical team member with responsibility of designing and manufacturing aerospace life support equipment.  Cutter will read and utilize blue prints and patterns required for pressure suit construction.  Cutter will cut material to order while following details written procedures, including material traceability and handling.

raw_data.title: Stitcher
raw_data.description: Performs stitching of a variety of textiles used in the fabrication of aerospace life support equipment.  Demonstrate repeated precision utilizing all necessary stitching techniques which may include unique training not provided elsewhere.  Read and utilize patterns, industrial drawings, and samples as required for pressure suit construction. Proficiency with U.S. measuring system. The stitcher will work as a member of a technical team or separately under direct supervision.  Stitcher will stitch material for production assembly and for research & development projects, while following organizational procedures.

raw_data.title: Cementer
raw_data.description: Performs tasking based on work orders and is under the direction of a technical team member with responsibility of designing and manufacturing aerospace life support equipment.  Cementer will mix solutions daily and apply to pressure suit components using unique processes developed specifically for this application. Requires ability to read and interpret diagrams and detailed written instructions.  Must be trained and demonstrate capability to consistently maintain the precision necessary.  Cementer will cement materials together for production assembly and for research & development projects, while following organizational procedures. Must document tasks as completed to ensure aerospace level traceability.

raw_data.title: Link Net Gridder
raw_data.description: Link net gridder is responsible for developing and fabricating link net patterns.  Link net is a uniquely softgoods design created and utilized for life support equipment not seen in any other industry.  Extensive training is necessary to develop the ability to perform this job precisely and efficiently.  Performs as directed on work orders and is under the direction of a technical team member.  Link net gridder also works directly with the design leads to create unique configurations.

raw_data.title: Link Net Assembly
raw_data.description: Link net assembler is responsible for assembling the link net pieces.  Link net is a uniquely softgoods design created and utilized for life support equipment not seen in any other industry.  Extensive training is necessary to develop the ability to perform this job precisely and efficiently.  Performs to specific work orders that require the ability to read and apply detailed written instructions, plans, and schematics.  Link net assembler works as a member of a technical team for aerospace production as well as research and development.

raw_data.title: Material Coordinator
raw_data.description: Responsible for the acquisition and inventory management of materials required for use in production/resell.

raw_data.title: Safety, Reliability & Quality Assurance (Designer)
raw_data.description: Carries out test procedures to ensure that all engineering or systems products and services meet minimum specified standards and end user requirements.  Thoroughly tests subsystems to ensure proper form, fit functional operation and freedom from defects.  Documents all problems and works to resolve them; reports progress on problem resolution to management.  SRQA also devises improvements to current procedures and models of possible future configurations.  Performs workflow analysis and recommends quality improvements.

raw_data.title: Project Engineer
raw_data.description: Knowledgeable of all aspects of a project/program including hardware, electronics, and logistics.  The project engineer will provide technical guidance and assistance to project/program personnel concerning day-to-day operations.  Responsible for keeping technical drawings and documentation updated; performs logistical support functions; prepares advanced planning for maintenance actions; and acquires materials and equipment.  Required to be familiar with CAD and word processing software and hardware for use in developing and updating technical documentation and must be capable of providing on the scene guidance and trouble shooting.

raw_data.title: Lead Systems Engineer (HOU)
raw_data.description: This position is considered an advanced level engineering position.  Responsibilities include supervising less experienced systems engineers and technical efforts, performing tasks that include, but are not limited to, requirements analysis, trade studies, developing conceptual designs, and special studies, analyses and failure investigations.  Additionally responsibilities include supporting and/or leading prototype development and first article testing, interface testing, independent verification and validation, demonstration and validation, preparing integrated logistics and life-cycle plans, system safety, quality assurance, education and training, and physical testing of the product or system.

raw_data.title: Electronic Technician
raw_data.description: Responsible for analyzing technical issues and problems.  Technician is responsible for repairing, maintaining and assembling of test electronics equipment specific to aerospace life support equipment.  Technician should have the ability to test and troubleshoot the equipment, read schematics, solder, and unsolder components utilizing techniques unique to the high altitude and space flight application.

raw_data.title: Project Monitor
raw_data.description: Monitor and report project status as required with emphasis on milestones and delivery requirements.  Coordinate schedules to facilitate completion of assigned contracts/projects.  Perform review, analysis, and interpretation of customer contracts and related documentation to include initial solicitations, Statements of Work (SOW), Work Breakdown Structures (WBS), Integrated Master Schedules (IMS), etc.  Manage day-to-day operational aspects of a project and scope and review deliverables prepared by team before passing to client.  Specific expertise may be required in Earned Value Management, cost estimation, or risk assessment and mitigation.

raw_data.title: Draftsman
raw_data.description: Produce renderings of new and current product designs.  Gains understanding of the scope and requirements of a project, and utilizes computer based systems to create both two dimensional and three dimensional renderings of the finished project.

raw_data.title: Helmet Technician
raw_data.description: Fabricate and overhaul all flight helmets related to aerospace life support systems.  Responsibilities include fabrication of helmet shells and all post form processing, prime and finish painting, use of specialized fixturing, and final assembly.  Skills also include the ability to interpret and use complex engineering drawings, creation of fabrication procedures, and various testing to verify the function of all parts and assemblies.

raw_data.title: Documentation Coordinator
raw_data.description: Maintain, update and archive master/support documents.  Responsible for disposing of confidential drawings, notes and documents that are not required to be kept.  The coordinator will maintain control configuration for all drawings, procedures, standards, and reports.
